{"word":"κατοικέω","slug":"κατοικέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κατοικέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to dwell in as a</i> <el>κάτοικος</el>, <i>to settle in, colonise</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>: generally, <i>to inhabit</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to settle, dwell</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—so in <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> and plup. <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>to have been settled, to dwell</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, of a state, <i>to be administered, governed</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> of cities, <i>to lie, be situate</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}